V{{Infobox scientist\u000a| name              = Anne Sjerp Troelstra\u000a| image             = <!--(filename only)-->\u000a| image_size        = \u000a| caption           = \u000a| birth_date        = {{birth date and age|1939|08|10|df=y}}\u000a| birth_place       = [[Maartensdijk]], [[Utrecht (province)|Utrecht]]\u000a| death_date        = \u000a| death_place       = \u000a| nationality       = Dutch\u000a| fields            = [[Mathematics]]\u000a| workplaces        = [[University of Amsterdam]]\u000a| alma_mater        = University of Amsterdam\u000a| doctoral_advisor  = [[Arend Heyting]]\u000a| doctoral_students = [[Marc Bezem|Marcus Aloysius Bezem]]<br>[[Ieke Moerdijk]]<br>[[Daniel Leivant]]<br>[[Laurina Verbrugge]]\u000a| known_for         = \u000a| awards            = \u000a}}\u000a'''Anne Sjerp Troelstra''' (born 10 August 1939) is [[Emeritus]] professor of [[pure mathematics]] and [[foundations of mathematics]] at the [[Institute for Logic, Language and Computation]] (ILLC) of the [[University of Amsterdam]].\u000a\u000aHe is a [[Constructivism (mathematics)|constructivist]] [[logician]], who has been influential in the development of [[intuitionistic logic]].<ref>[http://www.daimi.au.dk/~dp/Arkiv/Oktober2001/profil.html Daimiposten &ndash; Oktober 2001<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.ozsl.uu.nl/MartinLob.html MARTIN LÖB (1921&ndash;2006)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> With [[Georg Kreisel]], he was a developer of the theory of [[choice sequence]]s.<ref>{{Citation |first=Mathieu |last=Marion |title=Wittgenstein, Finitism, and the Foundations of Mathematics |year=1998 |location=New York |publisher=Oxford University Press |page=205 |isbn=0-19-823516-X }}.</ref> He also wrote one of the first texts on [[linear logic]],<ref>{{Citation |first=Herman Ruge |last=Jervell |title=Review: ''Lectures on Linear Logic'' by A. S. Troelstra |journal=Journal of Symbolic Logic |volume=61 |issue=1 |year=1996 |pages=336\u2013338 |doi=10.2307/2275616 }}.</ref> and with H. Schwichtenberg he co-wrote an important book on [[proof theory]].<ref>{{Citation |first=Roy |last=Dyckhoff |title=Review: ''Basic Proof Theory'' by A. S. Troelstra; H. Schwichtenberg |journal=Journal of Symbolic Logic |volume=63 |issue=4 |year=1998 |pages=1605\u20131606 |doi=10.2307/2586674 }}.</ref>\u000a\u000aHe became a member of the [[Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]] in 1976.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.knaw.nl/en/members/members/4881 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160214194705/https://www.knaw.nl/en/members/members/4881 |title=Anne Troelstra |publisher=Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences |date= |archive-date=14 February 2016 |accessdate=14 February 2016}}</ref>\u000a\u000a==Notes==\u000a<references/>\u000a\u000a==External links==\u000a*[http://www.uva.nl/over-de-uva/organisatie/medewerkers/content/t/r/a.s.troelstra/a.s.troelstra.html Homepage of A. S. Troelstra]\u000a*{{MathGenealogy |id=45627 }}\u000a\u000a{{Authority control}}\u000a\u000a{{DEFAULTSORT:Troelstra, Anne Sjerp}}\u000a[[Category:1939 births]]\u000a[[Category:Living people]]\u000a[[Category:Dutch mathematicians]]\u000a[[Category:Members of the Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]]\u000a[[Category:People from De Bilt]]\u000a[[Category:University of Amsterdam alumni]]\u000a[[Category:University of Amsterdam faculty]]\u000a\u000a\u000a{{netherlands-scientist-stub}}\u000a{{europe-mathematician-stub}}
